#: src/rust-2018/cargo-and-crates-io/cargo-rustc-for-passing-arbitrary-flags-to-rustc.md:1
msgid "`cargo rustc` for passing arbitrary flags to rustc"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/cargo-and-crates-io/cargo-rustc-for-passing-arbitrary-flags-to-rustc.md:3
msgid ""
"![Minimum Rust version: 1.1](https://img.shields.io/badge/"
"Minimum%20Rust%20Version-1.1-brightgreen.svg)"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/cargo-and-crates-io/cargo-rustc-for-passing-arbitrary-flags-to-rustc.md:5
msgid ""
"`cargo rustc` is a new subcommand for Cargo that allows you to pass "
"arbitrary `rustc` flags through Cargo."
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/cargo-and-crates-io/cargo-rustc-for-passing-arbitrary-flags-to-rustc.md:8
msgid ""
"For example, Cargo does not have a way to pass unstable flags built-in. But "
"if we'd like to use `print-type-sizes` to see what layout information our "
"types have, we can run this:"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/cargo-and-crates-io/cargo-rustc-for-passing-arbitrary-flags-to-rustc.md:16
msgid "And we'll get a bunch of output describing the size of our types."
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/cargo-and-crates-io/cargo-rustc-for-passing-arbitrary-flags-to-rustc.md:18
msgid "Note"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/cargo-and-crates-io/cargo-rustc-for-passing-arbitrary-flags-to-rustc.md:20
msgid ""
"`cargo rustc` only passes these flags to invocations of your crate, and not "
"to any `rustc` invocations used to build dependencies. If you'd like to do "
"that, see `$RUSTFLAGS`."
msgstr ""
